          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Recognize that their rejection does not erase your value in God's eyes. Jesus Himself was rejected as the cornerstone-the very thing the building needed most. Your rejection may reveal their blindness, not your worthlessness. Find community with people who see your whole picture, not just your flaws. Pursue healing and restoration, not isolation. And ask yourself: have you rejected yourself? Because if you have, that is the voice you need to challenge first. God has not rejected you. Stop accepting others' rejection as final."
